<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-08T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="695" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–854: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-08T13:00:00+01:00">June 8, 1954—1
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 398. Repeated information
                                London 254, Paris 397, Bangkok 18, <gloss target="#t_USUN1">Usun</gloss> 12. Reference <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 368.<note n="1" xml:id="d695fn1">Dated June 7,
                                        <ref target="#pg_1058">p. 1058</ref>.</note>
                                <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> is not returning until
                                just prior to Indochina plenary this afternoon, and <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> is leaving for Paris
                                immediately following the plenary. I believe I can obtain <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>’s agreement instruct
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Hoppenot</persName> to agree to
                                language which will not specifically restrict <gloss target="#t_POC1">POC</gloss> operations to Thailand, and will
                                make attempt do so before <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>’s departure today. However, in view of
                                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>’s and <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>’s schedules, there will be
                                no opportunity work out and agree on specific language prior to
                                    Friday.<note n="2" xml:id="d695fn2">June 11.</note></p>
                            <p>As I have previously said, I see grave dangers in negotiating this
                                subject here and had hoped that further negotiations and drafting
                                could be centered in New York and Washington.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SWB1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>